Subject: StealthAudit - Custom Email Counts returning no data
Description: In StealthAudit we have a custom job that lets our claims department know how many emails were sent the previous mouth.  This month the counts were all zeros.   I could use some assistance on figuring out how to fix this.
What_We_Know__c:
The exchange On-premise is no longer collecting data because the customer migrated to Office365.
Some jobs that used to work with Exchange On-prem are not supported on Exchange Online, like the HUB Metrics group.
The customer extensively used this "HUB Metrics" group to collect data and is now looking for an alternative.

After fixing the Autodiscover with this
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/z-kb-articles-salesforce/page/kA0Qk0000001hVxKAI.html

1-16-25
We created a new analysis to pull data from the Mailflow job in order to present the same data this custom job was using the older collecters for.

3-19 
Ran 2 scripts to attempt to pull the old on  prem exchange data from the tables.
We will see if that clears up the Reporting console numbers.
Next_Steps__c: Wait on results of new script and review of reports.
Solution_Comment__c: Assisted in clearing old data and verifiying reports publishing as planned.
